  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({"@context":"https://schema.org","@type":"Article","headline":"Scrabble Ratings Explained — How Rankings Work","description":"Understand how Scrabble ratings work. Learn about the Elo-like rating system, how points are gained and lost, what ratings mean for division placement, and how to track your improvement.","datePublished":"2026-06-14","author":{"@type":"Organization","name":"ScrabbleWordsFinder.com","url":"https://www.scrabblewordsfinder.com"},"publisher":{"@type":"Organization","name":"ScrabbleWordsFinder.com"},"mainEntityOfPage":{"@type":"WebPage","@id":"https://www.scrabblewordsfinder.com/blog/scrabble-ratings-explained"}})} />
  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({"@context":"https://schema.org","@type":"FAQPage","mainEntity":[{"@type":"Question","name":"How does the Scrabble rating system work?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Scrabble uses an Elo-like rating system where you gain points for wins and lose points for losses. The amount gained or lost depends on the rating difference between you and your opponent. Beating a higher-rated player earns more points than beating a lower-rated one. New players start around 500-800 and the scale extends beyond 2100 for elite players."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"What is a good Scrabble rating?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Ratings vary by region, but generally: under 900 is beginner, 900-1200 is intermediate, 1200-1600 is advanced club player, 1600-1900 is expert, and 2000+ is elite or world-class. A rating of 1200 means you can consistently win at club level and compete respectably in tournaments."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"How many games does it take to get a stable Scrabble rating?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Most rating systems require 10-20 rated games before your rating stabilizes. Initial games have higher volatility — your rating can swing 50-100 points per game. After 20-30 games, swings decrease to 5-15 points per game, giving a more accurate picture of your true skill level."}}]})} />

